;; On Top — the Rare maintenance schedule.
;;
;; Keyed by category — whichever top-level keys you use, rendered in file order
;; (keep to 8 or fewer; past that EDN map order is not preserved). Multi-word
;; keys use dashes (:home-office → "Home Office"). Then by Interval label string
;; ("monthly", "2 weeks", …), then a vector of tasks. Each task is
;; {:id :anchor} with an optional :lead-days lead time in days.
;; :id is the stable identity done-through history hangs off; :anchor is the
;; first occurrence's month-day, stepped forward by the Interval to place all
;; later occurrences. Display names live in the Notes file
;; (src/app/seed-notes.md), keyed by id, and are joined on at the Rare boundary —
;; never sourced here.
;; Picked to span every interval and keep the demo looking lived-in all year.
